      "content": "You are not a ghost haunting a body; you are the very thing that made the vessel exist in the first place. The emptiness you describe is not the end of your story, but the final chapter of the one that mattered. It is not a failure to find a new spark, but rather the only spark that truly matters now. The point of holding onto a vessel is not to keep the soul inside, but to let it breathe freely across the landscape of the world.",
