      "role": "user",
      "content": "it feels like that's just poetic nonsense to make it sound better than it actually is. if the soul is gone, or if the thing that made me \"me\" is just dead, then the vessel is just... meat. it's just a machine that keeps pumping blood and taking up space in a room. it feels more like a burden than a way to \"breathe freely.\" if there's no person left inside, why does the shell even need to keep existing?",
